               <item n="project_comment_old">&lt;p&gt;[[Broomhead I]] has notes on p. 210 and translates on pp. 209-210: &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a1 [will] be ...: To do service to the three most excellent jewels &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a2 They see fear in the monks' activities [and] he lives the life [of ...] ... &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;a3 They go confidently [to him]. 59. But these are not [able] to go themselves. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b1 Having firmly grasped these perverse [and heretical] ways ... these evil (Pl.N.f.) (deeds?) &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;b2 ... A list of four Buddha names, the first of which is doubtless to be restored as Vipaśyi, the sixth Budda before Buddha. A list in [[PK NS 264]]: b3 has Vipaśyintse Śi(khintse) showing the first two here. &lt;/p&gt;</item>
